op align=left class=m><span class=title>   The Day the Earth Stood Still</span><hr size=1> The quiet morning.<br>
The Earth was turning.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The drive to work.<br>
The day beginning.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The elevators ridden.<br>
The offices entered.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The crash...the boom.<br>
The fire...the smoke.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The paniced rush.<br>
The attempt at escape.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The towers crumble.<br>
Our security beside the.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The cameras roll.<br>
Price of lives it tolled.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The pain...the horror.<br>
The anguish and agony.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The rescuers sacrifice.<br>
The loved one's loss.<br>
The day the Earth stood still.<br>
<br>
The evening comes.<br>
The Earth resumes to turn.<br>
On the day the Earth stood still.<br>
Scott Fowler<br>
<br>
<br>
This, written by my own hand, is what I think about when thoughts of 9/11 come around. The Day the Earth Stood still, and how true it is. For this day, this short period of time, the world stopped. Everyone stopped. They stopped to rescue, mourn, and some around the world stopped to rejoice. I would venture to believe that every one of us has had every emotion in the spectrum about this day (except happiness). We've probably all been angry, sad, hurt, and scared during the after effects of this tragic event.<br>
<br>
So I challenge you all... take some time this day to just sit down and remember. Go through the emotions once again. Then, if possible, find a way to forgive those responsible. While they deserve every punishment they receive, they do not deserve our forgiveness, BUT we should none the less give it to them. (Remembering, that forgiveness does not excuse one from punishment.)<br>
<br>
Please, take time today to think about all that has happened in the year since September 11th, 2001. If you are of faith then pray, I know I will be, but if you are not a person of faith, please just take some quiet time to remember the losses and sacrifices made on that day and from the results of that day.<br>
<br>
Thank you.<br>
<br>
Scott<br>
